This paper is about generating adversarial examples for deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new optimization technique for synthesizing adversarial examples. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the experiments are conducted on image recognition models and datasets. The third most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper deals with the security of deep learning models against adversarial attacks. The fourth most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper proposes a new approach to solving a problem in AI. The fifth most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper uses genetic algorithms for optimization.
